Remove dependency on PX4-Autopilot

When microxrceddsclient is built for PX4 it includes the PX4 drv_hrt.h
for access to hrt_absolute_time.

We replace the include on the header with a external function prototype.

Signed-off-By: Rob Woolley <rob.woolley@windriver.com>

diff --git a/src/c/util/time.c b/src/c/util/time.c
index 12aec56..b9ffcdc 100644
--- a/src/c/util/time.c
+++ b/src/c/util/time.c
@@ -21,7 +21,15 @@
 #endif
 
 #define __EXPORT __attribute__ ((visibility ("default")))
-#include <drivers/drv_hrt.h>
+/**
+ * Absolute time, in microsecond units.
+ *
+ * Absolute time is measured from some arbitrary epoch shortly after
+ * system startup.  It should never wrap or go backwards.
+ */
+typedef uint64_t	hrt_abstime;
+
+__EXPORT extern hrt_abstime hrt_absolute_time(void);
 
 #endif // PX4
 
